CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 23, 1957, pg. A17 reads: " "King And Queen" - Dr. and Mrs. Charles C. (?) Bookert reigned as "Chi King and Queen" at he swank Chi Delta Mu ball, held at Webster Hall Hotel. They are surrounded by other members of the fraternity. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Charles Bookert and Mrs. Bookert wearing ermine capes and crowns, surrounded by fraternity members wearing tuxedos, including Dr. Reginald Dixon on far right, in Webster Hall for Chi Delta Mu formal ball
